name: Baked Parmesan Dip
author: Anonymous
summary: Put a bubbling hot spin on traditional spinach dip with this crowd pleaser. Substitute spinach with artichoke hearts for an extra twist.
ingredients: 1 (10 ounce) package frozen chopped spinach, thawed
1 cup reduced-fat or regular Safeway SELECT™ Mayonnaise
2 (8 ounce) Safeway SELECT™ Artisan Baguettes, thinly sliced
directions: With a mixer, beat spinach, mayonnaise, cream cheese, onion, garlic, 1 cup of the parmesan cheese, and pepper until thoroughly combined
Mound mixture in a 3- to 4-cup baking dish
Sprinkle evenly with 2 tablespoons parmesan cheese and paprika
Bake in a 350 degrees F oven until hot in center and lightly browned on top, 25 to 30 minutes
Serve hot to spread on baguette slices
